Package game.briefings

Class Report

java.lang.Object
game.briefings.Report
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Report>
public class Report
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Report>
The Report class represents a detailed record of a game simulation or mission. It encapsulates information such as the mission type, player involved, mission details, timing, entry point, trajectories, enemies encountered, and backpack details. The report is used to track the progress, status, and outcomes of a mission or game session.

  • Constructor Details

    • Report

      public Report​(java.lang.String type, Player player, Mission mission)
      Constructs a new Report instance with the specified type, player, and mission. This constructor initializes the report with a unique simulation ID, a timestamp, and references to the player and mission involved. It also initializes several collections to track various aspects of the mission such as trajectory paths and enemy states.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of the report (e.g., simulation, mission result)
      player - the Player instance associated with the report
      mission - the Mission instance associated with the report

    • setBackPackSize

      public void setBackPackSize​(int backPackSize)
      Updates the size of the backpack based on the provided value. The backpack size is represented as a descriptive string corresponding to the given integer value.
      Parameters:
      backPackSize - an integer representing the backpack size. Acceptable values are: 0 - "Try hard mode (No backpack)" 1 - "Small Backpack" 2 - "Medium Backpack" 5 - "Big Backpack" Any other value results in "No backPack used".

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo​(Report o)
      Compares this report object to another report object for order based on the player's current health. The comparison is done in descending order, where higher current health comes first.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Report>
      Parameters:
      o - the other Report object to be compared
      Returns:
      a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this report's player has less than, equal to, or greater current health compared to the other report's player

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Returns a string representation of the Report object. The string contains details about the report, including the mission version, simulation ID, timestamp, type, mission status, player information, backpack size, and various trajectory and mission-related details.
      Overrides:
      toString in class java.lang.Object
      Returns:
